==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stink
<hw>Stink</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Stunk</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>, <conjf>Stank</conjf>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Stinking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>stinkan</ets> to have
a smell (whether good or bad); akin to OHG. <ets>stinchan</ets>, G. & D.
<ets>stinken</ets> to stink; of uncertain origin; cf. Icel.
<ets>st⟦oum⟧kkva</ets> to leap, to spring, Goth. <ets>stigqan</ets> to
push, strike, or Gr. <?/ rancid. Cf. <er>Stench</er>.]</ety> <def>To
emit a strong, offensive smell; to send out a disgusting odor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stink</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stink
<hw>Stink</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cause to stink; to affect by a
stink.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stink</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Stink
<hw>Stink</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>stinc</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
strong, offensive smell; a disgusting odor; a stench.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fire stink</b></col>. <cd>See under <er>Fire</er>.</cd>
-- <col><b>Stink-fire lance</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Lance</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Stink rat</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>,
<cd>the musk turtle.</cd> <mark>[Local, U.S.]</mark> -- <col><b>Stink
shad</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the gizzard shad.</cd>
<mark>[Local, U.S.]</mark> -- <col><b>Stink trap</b></col>, <cd>a stench
trap. See under <er>Stench</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stinkard</ent>⟦br⟧
